#X text 45 13 The "envelope filter" technique uses an envelope to control the filter frequency. It's the main technique for subtractive synthesis \, widely common in any classic synth. Here we have two envelopes \, one to control the amplitude and another to control the filter. The filter center frequency is set in Hz but converted to MIDI so it can be modulated by the envelope. The envelope is set to linear but note that it's modulating the pitch in semitones \, which is then converted to linear frequency in hertz via [mtof~]. If the semitonws value is negative \, the sweep goes from a lower frequency up to the center one., f 73;
